 :tx/rationale "Create task: CTP-5: Compiler orchestrator — compile_seed replaces assemble_seed as the primary seed generation path (INV-SEED-001, INV-SEED-005, INV-BUDGET-006). BACKGROUND: The four compilation phases (CTP-1..4) produce independent sections. The orchestrator sequences them, manages the token budget across sections, and produces the final SeedOutput. Budget allocation: priors(10%) + constraints(20%) + demonstration(30%) + directive(20%) + store summary(20%). If a section underflows, excess budget flows to the next section. If total exceeds budget, demonstration is compressed first (it's the most compressible). APPROACH: compile_seed(store, task, budget, agent) -> SeedOutput: (1) Allocate sub-budgets. (2) Call compile_priors, compile_constraints, compile_demonstrations, compile_directives. (3) Assemble: priors at top (highest k* position), then constraints, then demonstration, then directive, then store summary (reuse existing store_summary logic). (4) Measure total tokens. If over budget, truncate demonstration first, then constraints. Never truncate priors or directive (they're the action). (5) Return SeedOutput with all existing fields populated. ACCEPTANCE: (A) compile_seed output fits within budget for any budget >= 200. (B) Priors section always present (never truncated). (C) Directive section always present. (D) compile_seed achieves >= 1.5x semantic density vs assemble_seed at same budget. (E) Existing braid seed CLI works unchanged (wire compile_seed as new default). DEPENDS-ON: CTP-2, CTP-3, CTP-4. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/seed.rs"
